Fantastic cake that was perfect as a tea-time snack. I used only 1 cup of sugar and only 1 stick of butter, but it turned out fluffy, sweet, and delicious. I also used part cake flour, because I ran out of regular flour. I used fresh rather than frozen blueberries. Because the recipe warned they would sink to the bottom, I didn't mix them into the batter; I poured the batter into the cake pan, then dropped the blueberries onto the top of the batter and pushed them down until they were mostly just barely submerged in batter. This turned out really well; they didn't sink much, so when I turned the cake out onto a dish, the bottom of the cake had a nice, juicy rim of blueberries. That's definitely how I'll make it from now on. I served it a few times with blueberry jam heated with a bit of pear liqueur. Delicious!

