To address the cook from Wilson, NC, I also spoon my flour into a dry measuring cup and level with the back of a knife. I've read that when you dip your measuring cup into the flour, you run the risk of packing too much flour into the cup, and thus, into your recipe. (P.S. Recipe looks like a real nice way to use up leftover buttermilk!) :)

