You could use lemon zest, and mix the powdered sugar w/ some lemon juice to drizzle over the cake after it cools. If you dredge fresh blueberries in flour (or mix them into the flour mixture before adding the liquid) they won't sink to the bottom. I used Williams-Sonoma's cake pan coating, and the cake didn't stick...also used a non-stick pan.

